@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "CancellationToken Demo";
}

<h1>CancellationToken — Live Demo</h1>
<p class="subtitle">Each scenario logs to the <strong>server console</strong>. Watch it as you click Start / Cancel / close the tab.</p>

<!-- SCENARIO 1 -->
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <span class="badge">Scenario 1</span>
        <h2>Basic Request Cancellation</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Starts a <strong>10-second simulated DB query</strong>. Close the browser tab or click Cancel — the server stops immediately.</p>
    <div class="log-box" id="log1">Waiting to start...</div>
    <div class="actions">
        <button class="btn-start" onclick="startScenario(1, '/Demo/SlowQuery')">▶ Start</button>
        <button class="btn-cancel" onclick="cancelScenario(1)" disabled>■ Cancel</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">
        <strong>Server logs to watch:</strong><br />
        🟡 SlowQuery started → <em>(close tab or cancel)</em> → 🚫 SlowQuery CANCELLED
    </div>
</div>

<!-- SCENARIO 2 -->
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <span class="badge">Scenario 2</span>
        <h2>Multi-Step Pipeline</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Runs <strong>5 steps, 2 seconds each</strong>. Cancel between any step — the remaining steps are skipped entirely.</p>
    <div class="log-box" id="log2">Waiting to start...</div>
    <div class="actions">
        <button class="btn-start" onclick="startScenario(2, '/Demo/MultiStep')">▶ Start</button>
        <button class="btn-cancel" onclick="cancelScenario(2)" disabled>■ Cancel</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">
        <strong>Key code:</strong> <code>ct.ThrowIfCancellationRequested()</code> before each step.
    </div>
</div>

<!-- SCENARIO 3 -->
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <span class="badge">Scenario 3</span>
        <h2>Timeout Cancellation</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Work takes <strong>8 seconds</strong> but a <strong>5-second timeout</strong> is set via <code>CreateLinkedTokenSource</code>. Always times out — no need to manually cancel.</p>
    <div class="log-box" id="log3">Waiting to start...</div>
    <div class="actions">
        <button class="btn-start" onclick="startScenario(3, '/Demo/WithTimeout')">▶ Start</button>
        <button class="btn-cancel" onclick="cancelScenario(3)" disabled>■ Cancel (or just wait)</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">
        <strong>Key code:</strong> <code>when (timeoutCts.IsCancellationRequested)</code> — distinguishes timeout vs disconnect.
    </div>
</div>

<!-- SCENARIO 4 -->
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">
        <span class="badge">Scenario 4</span>
        <h2>Manual Cancel Button</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Runs for <strong>15 seconds</strong>, logging every second. Click Cancel at any point — server stops at the exact second you cancel.</p>
    <div class="log-box" id="log4">Waiting to start...</div>
    <div class="actions">
        <button class="btn-start" onclick="startScenario(4, '/Demo/ManualCancel')">▶ Start</button>
        <button class="btn-cancel" onclick="cancelScenario(4)" disabled>■ Cancel</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">
        <strong>Watch the console</strong> — logs stop the moment you click Cancel. Not after the current sleep finishes.
    </div>
</div>

<!-- SCENARIO 5 -->
<div class="card bad">
    <div class="card-header">
        <span class="badge bad-badge">Scenario 5 — ❌ Bad Pattern</span>
        <h2>Fire and Forget (Token NOT Passed)</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Starts a 10-second task <strong>without passing the CancellationToken</strong>. Cancel or close the tab — the server <strong>keeps running anyway</strong>.</p>
    <div class="log-box" id="log5">Waiting to start...</div>
    <div class="actions">
        <button class="btn-start" onclick="startScenario(5, '/Demo/FireAndForget')">▶ Start</button>
        <button class="btn-cancel" onclick="cancelScenario(5)" disabled>■ Cancel (server ignores it)</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tip bad-tip">
        <strong>Watch the console</strong> — even after Cancel, the server logs "Completed" 10 seconds later. This wastes DB connections and threads.
    </div>
</div>
